events.name: マップ移動（ハタヤキ村ヘ）

parameters:
We have received a report that this village has been attacked.
Until safety is confirmed, entry is prohibited.

Good work. It seems like the reconstruction of this village will
be impossible for a while.

events.name: マップ移動（ハタヤキ村ヘ）

parameters:
We have received a report that this village has been attacked.
Until safety is confirmed, entry is prohibited.
The excavation marks are severe, this land is already...
\SE[2] The back mountain is not this way. \SM[double] Up. Up.

I don't even flinch at the children's tackles... I'll try doing a
quick tackle with the Q button too. Well... it's a little
embarrassing though.
It's a training scarecrow. But... everyone who used it is gone.
\SE[2] The back mountain is not this way. \SM[double] Up. Up.

I don't even flinch at the children's tackles... I'll try doing a
quick tackle with the Q button too. Well... it's a little
embarrassing though.
It's a training scarecrow. \!... Everyone who used it is gone.

I'm glad there was a bonfire.... I was just one step away from
being incapacitated in battle. You should be careful too!

Phew... As a magic user, MP is my lifeline, so when it's running
low, I get really nervous...

It's a scarecrow to keep away animals. It has been protecting the
village since I was a child.

The response is too cold... It seems that this scarecrow is not
interested in a tackle....

events.name: タックル教わりイベント

parameters:
\SE[19]The child is tackling.... I hope \SE[17] they're okay. I
wonder what happened...?

Oh, it's Laura. I was teaching the children in order to spread
the new technology that was created in the city.

This is a special move that will become essential from now on.
It's called the Quick Tackle, do you already know about it?

\SE[17]The special move from the city...! \SE[19]The essential
Quick Tackle...!?

Hoho, that's right! I'll teach it to Laura too! It's so strong
that I think you'll be surprised!

Hoho...! It's no good to pretend to know everything! I will teach
it to Laura too, straight from me!

Alright, Laura!! What do you think is the strongest action in
battle?
Endure and wear down with super durability!
Mow them down with super fast attacks!

Hmm, it's not about brute force!! It's natural to get excited
when you see big numbers...! But this time, it's different!

Not the 'sticky' type...!! Are you the type to fight for about an
hour, little by little...! \!... You're not a 'modern person'!
But this time, it's different!

Hmmm, not 'impatient'!! If you attack from behind, there won't
even be a need for 'battle', right?! ...Could it be, you're the
type to attack while transforming...?

Yes, being honest is the best!! When you don't understand, it's
good to rely on someone else!! \!...Become someone who is good at
teaching!

Well, it's a case-by-case basis! There's no right answer, you
know!! Flexibility and diligence are important!

This time, it's all about mowing down with super fast attacks!
\!The theme is to strike before getting struck, and that's the
strongest move! \!In times like that, it's the perfect moment for
the Quick Tackle!

There are monsters wandering in the forest, you know? Use the Q
button to perform a Quick Tackle on them! If you succeed, you'll
be able to launch a preemptive attack! It will give you a huge
advantage, so make sure to use it actively!

\SE[15] Quick Tackle with the [Q button]... \SE[14] To
[preemptively] and [unilaterally attack]... I see!

Yes, I have certainly imparted my knowledge!! \.If the 'settings'
or 'devices' are different...!\I won't understand, for sure!!
\!Even if it's not ideal, we'll manage somehow, so let's figure
it out!

Listen up, Laura. Use the Q button to perform a Quick Tackle.
Since you tend to forget, I'll write it on the palm of your hand!

It's good to practice with that scarecrow over there. Only when
you succeed will it turn into a battle. When it goes whoosh!! and
says one turn break!!, that means you've succeeded...!!
